    • Constructor Detail

      • MoonOrbitalElement

        public MoonOrbitalElement()
        Constructs an empty moon orbital object.

      • MoonOrbitalElement

        public MoonOrbitalElement(double sma,
                  double mean_lon,
                  double ecc,
                  double peri_lon,
                  double asc_node_lon,
                  double incl,
                  double ref_time)
        Constructs a moon orbit object giving the values of the main fields. Argument of periapsis is set to periapsis longitude minus ascending node longitude. Mean anomaly is set to mean longitude minus periapsis longitude. Mean motion is set to Constant.GAUSS / (sma * Math.sqrt(sma), assuming a massless object in planetocentric orbit. sma = semimajor axis.

        Is is necessary to set also the reference equinox to get correct ephemeris.

        Parameters:
        sma - Semimajor axis in AU.
        mean_lon - Mean Longitude in radians.
        ecc - Eccentricity.
        peri_lon - Periapsis longitude in radians.
        asc_node_lon - Longitude of ascensing node in radians.
        incl - Inclination in radians.
        ref_time - Reference time (usually perihelion time) as a Julian day.

        Constructs a moon orbit object giving the values of all the fields.
        Parameters:
        nom - Name of the object
        sma - Semimajor axis in AU.
        mean_anom - Mean anomaly in radians.
        ecc - Eccentricity.
        arg_peri - Argument of periapsis in radians.
        asc_node_lon - Longitude of ascensing node in radians.
        incl - Inclination in radians.
        ref_time - Reference time (usually perihelion time) as a Julian day.
        motion - Mean motion in radians/day.
        equinox - Reference equinox as a Julian day.
        init_time - Begin of applicable time as a Julian day.
        final_time - End of applicable time as a Julian day.
        ref_plane - Reference plane for the elements.
        Laplace_RA - Right ascension of the Laplace local plane.
        Laplace_DEC - Declination of the Laplace local plane.
        prec_peri - Precession of the periapsis, rad/day.
        prec_node - Precession of the ascending node, rad/day.
        ref_ephem - Ephemeris reference.

      • MoonOrbitalElement

        public MoonOrbitalElement(java.lang.String[] elementsFromHorizons,
                  java.lang.String name,
                  Target.TARGET motherPlanet)
        Constructor for a set of elements as returned by Horizons in case of elements referred to 'Body Mean Equator and Node of Date'. These elements should not be used more than 2 years after or before the reference time of the elements.
        Parameters:
        elementsFromHorizons - Array of 5 strings with the elements.
        name - The name of the satellite.
        motherPlanet - The planet this satellite is orbiting around.
